ants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Soddington","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Nottinghamshire and Lincolnshire): habitational name from any of various places, for example in Cheshire, Derbyshire, Herefordshire, and Nottinghamshire, named Coddington, from the Old English personal name <i>Cot(t)a</i> + <i>-ing-</i> denoting association + <i>tūn</i> ‘settlement’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":17,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":26,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":61,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"William de Soddington I was born in 1198, in Worcestershire, England. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1301, in Worcester, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 103."},"et":{"1198–1301":"1198–1301","1220–1290":"1220–1290","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1301":"1301","1224":"1224","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","1290":"1290","Soddington, Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worcester, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1198–1301":"1198–1301","1220–1290":"1220–1290","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1301":"1301","1224":"1224","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","1290":"1290","Soddington, Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worcester, Worcestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1198–1301":"1198–1301","1220–1290":"1220–1290","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1301":"1301","1224":"1224","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","1290":"1290","Soddington, Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, Angleterre","Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worcester, Worcestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William de Soddington I est né en 11